                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d76">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hay</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Bridgman</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1899-03-04">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 4, 1899</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 76.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Referring to your unnumbered dispatch written at
                    Keene, N. H., August 16, last, I have to say that you press again, and urgently,
                    for the prompt trial or discharge of Capt. John S. Bowles, who was arrested
                    October 4, 1894.</p>
                <p>You will report the result of your action to the Department.</p>
                <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">John Hay.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
